TextExtractionObjectResponse.title: TextExtractionObjectResponse
TextExtractionObjectResponse.description:
The text extraction operation response when output_format is set to "object".

This class represents the structured response from a document text extraction operation,
containing both the extracted plain text and the complete document structure metadata
inherited from AssemblyJsonOutput.

Attributes:
    text (str): The extracted plain text content from the document. This is the 
               concatenated text from all pages and structures in reading order.
               Empty string if no text could be extracted.

Note:
    - This response type is used when DocProcSpec.output_format is set to 
      DocProcOutputFormat.object
    - For file reference responses, use TextExtractionResponse instead
    - The text field contains only plain text; structured data is in inherited fields

metadata.description: Document-level metadata including page count, title, author, language, and processing configuration. None if metadata extraction was not requested.

num_pages.title: Num Pages
num_pages.description: Total number of pages in the document

title.description: Document title as obtained from source document

language.title: Language
language.description: Determined by the lang specifier in the <html> tag, or <meta> tag

publication_date.description: Best effort bases for a publication date (may be the creation date)

subject.title: Subject
subject.description: Subject as obtained from the source document

charset.title: Charset
charset.description: Character set used for the output

output_tokens_flag.description: Whether individual tokens are output, as specified in the input to the API

output_bounding_boxes_flag.title: Output Bounding Boxes Flag
output_bounding_boxes_flag.description: Whether bounding boxes are output, as requested in the input to the API

page_image_width.title: Page Image Width
page_image_width.description: Width of the page in pixels, assuming the page is an image with default 72 DPI
